**User Cart Session in PHP**
==========================

This example demonstrates how to create a user cart session using PHP. We will use the `$_SESSION` superglobal and the `session_start()` function to store cart items.

**Setup**

Before we begin, make sure you have already set up sessions on your server. If not, add this line at the top of your script:
```php
<?php
session_start();
?>
```
**Cart Class**
-------------

Create a new file called `cart.php` with the following code:
```php
class Cart {
    private $items = array();

    public function addItem($product_id, $quantity) {
        if (isset($this->items[$product_id])) {
            $this->items[$product_id] += $quantity;
        } else {
            $this->items[$product_id] = $quantity;
        }
    }

    public function removeItem($product_id) {
        if (isset($this->items[$product_id])) {
            unset($this->items[$product_id]);
        }
    }

    public function getItems() {
        return $this->items;
    }
}
```
This class has methods to add, remove and retrieve items from the cart.

**Cart Session**
----------------

Create a new file called `cart-session.php` with the following code:
```php
<?php
// Include the Cart class
require_once 'cart.php';

// Create a new instance of the Cart class
$cart = new Cart();

// Set the cart session variables
$_SESSION['cart'] = $cart;

// Function to add item to cart
function addItemToCart($product_id, $quantity) {
    global $cart;
    $cart->addItem($product_id, $quantity);
}

// Function to remove item from cart
function removeItemFromCart($product_id) {
    global $cart;
    $cart->removeItem($product_id);
}

// Function to get items in cart
function getItemsInCart() {
    global $cart;
    return $cart->getItems();
}
?>
```
This script sets the cart session variables and provides functions to add, remove and retrieve items from the cart.

**Example Usage**
-----------------

To use this system, simply include the `cart-session.php` file in your PHP scripts. You can then use the following functions:

```php
// Add item to cart
addItemToCart(1, 2); // adds 2 of product with id 1

// Remove item from cart
removeItemFromCart(1);

// Get items in cart
$items = getItemsInCart();
print_r($items);
```
This will output the items in your cart.

Note: This is a basic implementation and you may want to add more features such as storing user ID, handling session timeout, etc. Also, make sure to secure your sessions by using HTTPS or other security measures.

